                        <summary>A collection of 2 books.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_764-item1">
                            <locus from="1a" to="57a">ff. 1a-57a</locus>
                            <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note type="content-genre">Ethics</note>
                            <note>In this work, under the impression of the number seven having sacred properties, seven sessions are prepared under the names of the seven days of the week.
                                In each session, the author writes some content related to the day, including some ethical narratives and hadiths, and historical stories about prophets.
                                At the beginning of each session, there are a Quranic verse and a hadith appropriate for the day on which a discussion is presented, 
                                followed by a narrative having the number seven mentioned somewhere as well as some supplementary ethical preachments and customs.  
                            </note>                            
                            <author key="person_12169967" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">ʿAyn al-Quḍāh, Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān, active 16th century‏</persName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="kunyah">Abū Naṣr</addName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara">عین‌القضاه، محمد ابن عبدالرحمن</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">ʿAyn al-Quz̤āt Hamadānī, Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān, - after 966 AH/1559</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara" type="alt">عین‌القضاة الهمدانی، محمد بن عبدالرحمن، -پس از ۹۶۶ق/۱۵۵۹</persName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara" type="kunyah">ابو نصر</addName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1002" change="#ids-cleanup">al-Sabʿīyāt fī mawāʿiẓ al-barīyāt</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara" key="work_1002" change="#ids-cleanup">السبعیات فی مواعظ البریات</title>
                            <note/>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ara" defective="true">… و الکوفه و الرابع العراق و الشام و الخراسان الی بلخ و الخامس الروم و ارمنیه…
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="ara">… ثم قال الله تعالی لجبرئیل قل لمحمد هل ترید منی الدیه فقال الرسول نعم الدیه تکون امتی والله اعلم تمت الرساله بعون الله تعالی.
                            </explicit>
